<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="393" pageId="19" pageNumber="392" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1873,2043]" box="[151,1155,1873,1900]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,396,1873,1899]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">Materials examined.</emphasis>
22 individuals; Stations Vas. 2(12), 5(1), 14(4), 20(1), 35(3), 39(1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1873,2043]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1909,1935]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">Distribution.</emphasis>
Atlanto-Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[600,955,1909,1935]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The species was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1352,1436,1909,1935]" name="Cyprus" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[238,499,1945,1971]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[343,405,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
. In Vasiliko Bay (current study), it is considered as a rare species (FI: 14.28 %).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1873,2043]" box="[151,1436,2017,2043]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,2017,2043]" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[260,473,2018,2043]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Maera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossimana">
<emphasis box="[260,473,2018,2043]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="392">Maera grossimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in association with algae and seagrasses, on rocks and stones, in sponges
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[198,1436,150,322]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
and in artificial substrata at 
<quantity box="[505,561,150,177]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" unit="m" value="35.0">35 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[643,862,151,177]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[741,796,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). In Vasiliko Bay it was found at 
<quantity box="[1227,1325,151,177]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" unit="m" value="34.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="20.0">20–48 m</quantity>
depth (32 + 
<quantity box="[222,269,187,213]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" unit="m" value="9.0">9 m</quantity>
), mainly in muddy sand and also sand substrates, with organic matter ranging between 
<geoCoordinate box="[1265,1327,187,213]" degrees="4.621" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" precision="55" value="4.621">4.621</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[1327,1404,187,213]" degrees="8.416" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" precision="55" value="-8.416">–8.416</geoCoordinate>
% (6.933 + 1.456 %) and in association with 
<emphasis box="[669,1103,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. V. Lamouroux" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[669,803,223,249]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">C. prolifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1845" box="[813,980,223,249]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="cylindracea">C. cylindracea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Ucria" box="[990,1103,223,249]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Cymodocea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delile" authorityYear="1813" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[1156,1284,223,248]" class="Liliopsida" family="Posidoniaceae" genus="Posidonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oceanica">
<emphasis box="[1156,1284,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">P. oceanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was found in stations classified according to the Bentix Index as in: “good” (2 stations, 5 individuals) and “moderate” (4 stations, 17 individuals). It was also recorded at fish farm stations (14 individuals).
</paragraph>
